Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThis afternoon, we have received reports from Mali that indicate the former President of the country is dead.
The Malian President had been in power for a long time until he was ousted in a coup that saw him almost lose his life in the incident that happened a couple of years ago.


Ibrahim Boubcar Keita
Ibrahim Boubcar Keita, died in a hospital this afternoon after being taken to the institution following a bout of illness that had attacked him.
Former Mali President Ibrahim Boubacar Keita with Uhuru Kenyatta during a past event in Nairobi
Family of the former president has confirmed the news terming the death unfortunate and a blow to the country after Ibrahim Boubacar ruled the country for many years.
The illness that had been afflicting the Former President has not yet been disclosed by the family at this moment.

During his reign, Ibrahim Boubacar enjoyed a close and healthy relationship with the country of Kenya and President Uhuru Kenyatta.
The former president has died at the age of 76 after having ruled Mali for many years before being ousted in a coup.
